section#Projects.projects
  .head
    | Projects
  h2 JavaScript Projects
  .card-container
    .card
      h4 Todo List (Javascript)
      img(src='sources/images/todo-list.jpg' alt='todo-list')
      p
        | A JavaScript todo-list is a web app for task management. It uses HTML for structure, and JavaScript
        | for interactivity, such as adding, completing, or removing tasks. Persistence can be achieved using
        | localStorage.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
    .card
      h4 Reminder App (Node Js)
      img(src='sources/images/Reminder-app.jpg' alt='ReminderApp')
      p
        | A Reminder App in Node.js can store tasks locally using the File System (fs) module. It schedules
        | reminders with node-cron and stores them in a local file. On receiving a task, it writes the task to
        | the file, and node-cron triggers the reminder.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
    .card
      h4 Password Generator (Javascript)
      img(src='sources/images/Password-Generator.jpg' alt='Password-Generator')
      p
        | A Password Generator in JavaScript uses the Math.random() function to create random passwords. It
        | allows users to select password length and character types (like uppercase, lowercase, numbers,
        | symbols).
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
    .card
      h4 Web-Based Notepad (JavaScript)
      img(src='sources/images/notepad.jpg' alt='Notepad')
      p
        | A Web-Based Notepad in JavaScript uses the localStorage object for storing and retrieving notes. It
        | allows users to write, save, and load notes directly in their browser. The application can also
        | include a password protection feature.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
    .card
      h4 Chatting App (Node Js And Socket.io)
      img(src='sources/images/Chatting App.jpg' alt='ChattingApp')
      p
        | A Chatting App in Node.js uses the Socket.IO library for real-time, bidirectional communication. It
        | allows users to send and receive messages instantly. The server, built with Node.js and Express.js,
        | handles incoming messages and broadcasts them to all connected clients.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
    .card
      h4 Weather App (Fetch API)
      img(src='sources/images/weather-project.jpg' alt='WeatherApp')
      p
        | A Weather App in JavaScript uses the Fetch API to retrieve weather data from a server. It sends
        | requests to a weather API, receives the data, and displays it to the user.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
  h2 Python Projects
  .card-container
    .card
      h4 Voice Assistant
      img(src='sources/images/voice-assistant.jpg' alt='voice-assistant')
      p
        | A Voice Assistant in Python uses the tkinter library for the GUI, speech_recognition for voice
        | recognition, and the OpenAI API for processing commands. It listens to user&rsquo;s voice, converts it to
        | text, sends it to OpenAI API, and performs the requested action.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
    .card
      h4 Billing App
      img(src='sources/images/billing-app.jpg' alt='billing-app')
      p
        | A Billing App in Python uses the tkinter library for GUI and MySQL for data integrity and storage. It
        | allows users to add items, calculate totals, and print bills using a printing.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
    .card
      h4 Pdf Merger
      img(src='sources/images/pdf-merger.jpg' alt='pdf-merger')
      p
        | A PDF Merger in Python uses the PyPDF2 module to merge up to 5 PDF files. It reads the files,
        | combines them into one, and writes the output to a new PDF file.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
    .card
      h4 Calculator
      img(src='sources/images/calculator.jpg' alt='calculator')
      p
        | A Calculator in Python uses the tkinter library for GUI. It allows users to perform basic arithmetic
        | operations like addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division.
      .btns
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Code Here
        a.label(href='#none' onclick="alert('No Path Defined');") Visit Website
  h2 Android Development Projects
  .card-container
    .card
      h4 Expense Tracker
      img(src='sources/images/Expense Tracker.jpg' alt='Expensetracker')
      p
        | An Expense Tracker in Java, built in Android Studio, uses SQLite for local data storage. It allows
        | users to log and categorize expenses, and view a summary of their spending with security each user
        | had to create an id while storing their expenses.
      .btns
